Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Systems Librarian (ILS and Website Specialist) (Title under review) Georgetown , ON Description Career Opportunity: Halton Hills Public LibraryOne (1) permanent full-time position Job Number: 202402The Town of Halton Hills is located on the Treaty Lands and Territory of the Mississauga of the Credit. Halton Hills, located 45 minutes from Toronto, is a unique and vibrant community with over 61,000 people and two well-established library branches. HHPL welcomes more than 250,000 visitors annually and more than 500,000 website visitors. We empower our patrons to learn, read, create, innovate, and discover at our library. We strive to remove barriers and to foster an atmosphere of learning, support, understanding, and inclusion. We employ over 35 professionally trained professionally trained library staff, who go above and beyond to provide stellar service to our patrons and deliver high-quality programs and relevant events. If this excites you, we’d love to continue the conversation.Position SummaryUnder the direction of the Manager of Content and Technologies, the Systems Librarian administers, maintains, and updates the library’s website and serves as the primary support to staff regarding day-to-day use of the Integrated Library System (ILS). This position also provides assistance to the Manager of Content and Technologies regarding ILS administration, provides support to the Information Technology Specialists and all staff on the use of library technology, and administers other library systems such as digital signage.Position ResponsibilitiesThese responsibilities indicate the general nature and level of work expected. It is not designed to cover or contain a comprehensive listing of activities, duties or responsibilities required by the incumbent. The Incumbent may be asked to perform other duties as required and as the nature of library services evolve. Website Administration and Marketing Serves as the Library’s webmaster and creates and updates website content in conjunction with the Manager of Content and Technologies and managers and supervisory staff. Assists with creating, editing, and publishing of social media content, website and other electronic marketing initiatives in conjunction with the Manager of Content and Technologies, the Marketing and Communications Specialist and other assigned staff. Supervises the website’s online calendar and advises other staff on its use and maintenance. Provides support to other staff regarding the website Content Management System (CMS), including booking module, form builder and events calendar.Integrated Library System (ILS) AdministrationAssist the Manager of Content and Technologies with the administration of the Integrated Library System (ILS), including creation of accounts, creation and maintenance of form templates, edits and updates to loan rules, and other associated parameters. Develops field mapping for ILS import templates. Develops 9xx field programming for MARC record ILS import templates. Works with library materials vendors to ensure correct settings are used for materials cataloguing and processing. Provides support to staff on the day-to-day use of the ILS. Maintains Electronic Resources and their integration with the ILS.Technical SupportWorks with the Information Technology Specialist and Manager of Content and Technologies to provide timely and professional on-site and telephone support to resolve hardware, software, network, and operating system issues. Provides on-boarding ILS and website training to new library employees. Creates documentation, user guides and tip sheets on new technologies and ILS modules for other staff. Assists with training other staff on new technologies and new ILS modules. In conjunction with the Manager of Content and Technologies and the I.T. Specialist, acts as a resource person for the use of technology in the library.Supervision Supervises Library Aides, college placement Library Technician students and volunteers.Hire, train, supervise and evaluate Library Aides, placement students and volunteers.Administration Maintains setting and administrative requirements of Circulating Electronics collections; supervises maintenance of these devices. Advises on innovative technology developments in the Library Information Technology field. Performs other job-related duties as assigned.QualificationsEssential Minimum education: Master of Library and Information Science or equivalent from an accredited institution. Course work in technology/systems/coding. Experience with ILS administration (knowledge of Clarivate Sierra considered an asset). Equivalent of three years’ experience working in a public library setting.Technical Competencies Proven technical skills working with new technologies, mobile devices, laptops, Chromebooks, eReaders, etc. Knowledge and understanding of HTML and CSS. Knowledge of library cataloguing standards and guidelines such as RDA, LCSH, etc. Knowledge of MARC and other machine-readable code. Proven technical skills in the areas of desktop software knowledge. Knowledge and understanding of Windows and iOS. Ability to present technical information clearly. Experience in recruiting, training, setting tasks, and supervising/coaching staff.DesirableKnowledge of a variety of content management systemsHours: 35 hours per week. May include evenings and weekends in both Acton and Georgetown branches.Salary Range: $76,934– $91,589 annually + competitive benefits and pensionApplication Deadline: Friday, April 5, 2024Start Date: April/May 2024To Apply:Qualified candidates may submit a detailed cover letter and resume in confidence to the library by 5:00 p.m. on Friday, April 5, 2024. Those candidates offered an interview will be required to provide the names and contact information of three references at that time.Please identify the title of the position and the job number that you are applying for in your cover letter and on the Resume Submission Portal where indicated. Please apply using only one method of application below. Online: Resumé Submission Portal (preferred) Mail: Lori Mazza Brenton, Executive Assistant Halton Hills Public Library 9 Church Street Georgetown, Ontario L7G 2A3RE: Systems Librarian – Content and Technologies We thank all those who apply but advise that only those applicants selected for an interview will be contacted. The Halton Hills Public Library is an equal opportunity employer. Accommodations are available for all parts of the recruitment process. If contacted for an interview, please advise the Library’s Executive Assistant at 905-873-2681 Ext. 2523 of any measures you feel you need to enable you to be assessed in a fair and equitable manner. Information received relating to accommodation measures will be addressed confidentially. Compensation $76,934– $91,589 annually Closes: 5 April, 2024 Halton Hills Public Library Georgetown , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
