resources, support, and communicate with branch libraries regarding collections, acquisitions, processing, library systems, and digital resources. Work collaboratively with Regional Director, Branch Supervisor, and Office Manager to develop and implement library policy, procedures, and guidelines. Assist in the compilation and distribution of the regional newsletter in conjunction with Regional Director and Branch Supervisor. Assist in the development and maintenance of branch manual content in conjunction with Regional Director and Branch Supervisor. Direct acquisitions and processing staff to facilitate these duties as required. Perform other duties as assigned. Qualifications:MLIS or other relevant graduate degreeAt least two years of acquisitions and purchasing experienceAt least two years of library collections experience A candidate working on their MLIS,
